Package org.strykeforce.deadeye

Class Deadeye<T extends TargetData>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.strykeforce.deadeye.Deadeye<T>
  • public class Deadeye<T extends TargetData>
extends Object
    Objects of the Deadeye class represent a connection to a Deadeye camera pipeline. It provides methods to configure and control the camera and to receive target data.

    To use this class make sure that the TargetData type that you construct this class with is the same as the Deadeye pipeline target data type. These include:

    • UprightRectTargetData when using an UprightRectPipeline
    • MinAreaRectTargetData when using a MinAreaRectPipeline
    • TargetListTargetData when using a TargetListPipeline

    For example, assuming our Deadeye camera "A0" uses an UprightRectPipeline, the constructor for this class is: 

     Deadeye<UprightRectTargetData> deadeye = new Deadeye<>("A0", UprightRectTargetData.class);

      • Deadeye

        public Deadeye​(String id,
               Class<T> cls,
               String linkAddress)
        Constructs an instance of Deadeye and initializes a connection to the associated Deadeye camera while manually specifying this client IP address.

        Manually specifying the client IP address should only be done once, for the first Deadeye instance initialized.

        Parameters:
        id - the camera id, i.e. the Deadeye unit letter followed by the camera number, for example "A0".
        cls - the TargetData Java class corresponding to the Deadeye pipeline type.
        linkAddress - the IP address the Deadeye daemon should send data to. If null, this client will reuse a previously configured address or attempt to automatically detect the correct IP address.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the cls is null
        IllegalArgumentException - if the id is not a letter followed by a 0-4 digit
        IllegalArgumentException - if the cls is not a valid TargetData class
        IllegalArgumentException - if the linkAddress supplied more than once and does not match address already in use

        Constructs an instance of Deadeye and initializes a connection to a Deadeye camera using a specified NetworkTables instance. This constructor is primarily for testing or when using a robot simulator.

        cls - the TargetData Java class corresponding to the Deadeye pipeline type.
        nti - the NetworkTables instance to connect through.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the cls or nti is null
        IllegalArgumentException - if the id is not a letter followed by a 0-4 digit
        IllegalArgumentException - if the cls is not a valid TargetData class

      • Deadeye

        public Deadeye​(String id,
               Class<T> cls,
               NetworkTableInstance nti,
               String linkAddress)
        Constructs an instance of Deadeye and initializes a connection to a Deadeye camera using a specified NetworkTables instance while manually specifying this client IP address. This constructor is primarily for testing or when using a robot simulator.

        Manually specifying the client IP address should only be done once, for the first Deadeye instance initialized.

        Parameters:
        id - the camera id, i.e. the Deadeye unit letter followed by the camera number, for example "A0".
        cls - the TargetData Java class corresponding to the Deadeye pipeline type.
        nti - the NetworkTables instance to connect through.
        linkAddress - the IP address the Deadeye daemon should send data to. If null, this client will attempt to automatically detect the correct IP address.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the cls or nti is null
        IllegalArgumentException - if the id is not a letter followed by a 0-4 digit
        IllegalArgumentException - if the cls is not a valid TargetData class
        IllegalArgumentException - if the linkAddress supplied more than once and does not match address already in use
